The paper is primarily focused on the design and analysis of algorithms for multi-finger binary search trees, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS). The paper also uses techniques from machine learning (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT) to develop its algorithms. Additionally, the paper discusses the theoretical optimality of splay trees, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.THE). Finally, the paper discusses the application of its results to serving queries that are close to recently accessed items, which is a topic in data mining (cs.DM) and machine learning (cs.LG).
